// =============================================================================
// core/types/mod.vr — Stdlib surface for advanced type-system features
// =============================================================================
// Layer: Standard Library / Types
// =============================================================================
//
// Type-system extensions that live BEYOND the Layer-0 base types
// (`core.base.{Maybe, Result, Heap, Shared, …}`) — these are the
// research-grade type machinery the language exposes for users
// who want to encode richer invariants in types:
//
//   * `poly_kinds.vr` — universe-polymorphic kind machinery for
//     higher-kinded protocols (HKT) and kind-indexed type families.
//
//   * `qtt.vr` — Quantitative Type Theory (Atkey-McBride) resource
//     tracking. Multiplicities `0` (erased) / `1` (linear) / `ω`
//     (unrestricted) annotated on type parameters and bindings,
//     gating the kernel's relevance + linearity checks.
//
//   * `two_level.vr` — Two-Level Type Theory (Annenkov-Capriotti-
//     Kraus-Sattler) — runs an inner cubical-univalent type theory
//     alongside an outer set-truncated meta-theory, so static-vs-
//     runtime hygiene is encoded in the type system rather than
//     the syntax of meta-programs.
//
// Usage is opt-in: most user code lives entirely at the base-types
// layer. These modules are surfaced so research-grade Verum
// programs (formal-methods libraries, dependently-typed kernels,
// resource-aware DSLs) can pull them in explicitly.
// =============================================================================

module core.types;

public module poly_kinds;
public module qtt;
public module two_level;
